"Reviewed

Type 2 diabetes mellitus
Developed abdominal discomfort with Glycomet GP2 and Jalra M

PTCA done in May 2021

FBS - 96 mg/dl
PPBS - 236 mg/dl
HbA1c - 8.3%

Balanoposthitis and polyuria with Tab. Oxra

Suggestion - 

Inj Lantus 42 units at bed time, subcutaneous, into the abdomen or thighs
Tab. Amaryl 2 mg 1-0-1, 30 minutes before food
Tab. Vildapride 50 mg 1-0-1 after food for diabetes
Tab. Pioz 7.5 mg 1-0-0 after food for diabetes
Tab. Cardivas 6.25 mg 1-0-0 after food
Tab. Deplatt CV 0-0-1 after food
Tab. Cilacar 10 mg 0-0-1 after food for BP
Tab. Prolomet XL 25 mg 1-0-0 after food for BP

Check PPBS every 15 days with glucometer
Review after 3 to 4 months with FBS, 2 hour PPBS and HbA1c

Opinion from Orthopedician for pain in knee joints

Target - 

FBS - 100 to 150 mg/dl
2 hour PPBS - 150 to 200  mg/dl
HbA1c - less than 8%

 "
